description: University of Michigan Kidney Epidemiology and Cost Center (UMKECC) is contracted with Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) to provide research and analysis of transplant and organ procurement data from the Scientific Registry of Transplant Recipients (SRTR) and to identify practice changes. UMKECC also assists CMS with oversight and administration of Survey and Certification activities.
title: Survey and Certification - Transplant Research
